manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MSI: For Gamers & Creators MSI is one of the most trusted names in gaming and esports with countless hours and significant resources invested into premier esports leagues and tier-1 gaming teams. By supporting and working with the best of the best, MSI is able to integrate competitive gaming knowledge and aspirations with technological innovation to create new products that shatter today's performance limits. MPG B760I EDGE WIFI Perform in Style The MPG B760I EDGE WIFI is a gaming oriented Mini-ITX motherboard constructed around the latest Intel B760 chipset that delivers both performance and style. Supports Intel Core 12th & 13th Gen Processors (LGA 1700) 2 x DDR5 DIMMs with Memory Boost: Dual Channel (96GB Max. / 7200MHz OC) 1 x PCIe 5.0 x16 slot Lightning Gen4 M.2 & M.2 Shield Frozr 7.1 HD Audio with Audio Boost Realtek 2.5G LAN, Intel Wi-Fi 6E & Bluetooth 5.3

B760 Chipset, 8 direct CPU power, Smart Cooling, PCI-E 5.0 x16 Slot Supports Intel Core 12th & 13th Gen Processors The MPG B760I EDGE WIFI motherboard supports 12th & 13th Gen Intel Core, Pentium Gold, and Celeron processors. Form Factor: Mini-ITXSocket Type: LGA 1700Chipset: Intel B760 Direct 8+1+1 phase VRM power with 90A DrMOS With its exclusive Core Boost technology, the MPG B760I EDGE WIFI is able to sustain heavy CPU power loads to support system-demanding game settings: Digital PWM IC8-Phase Direct CPU Power (DrMOS / 90A)1-Phase GT Power1-Phase AUX Power Integrated Cooling Features VRM Cooling: Features an extended heatsink and 7W/mK thermal pads and additional choke thermal pads for improved thermal dissipation.PCB Cooling: Premium 8-layer server-grade printed circuit design with 2 oz. thickened copper improves heat dissipation & reliability.SSD Cooling: M.2 Shield Frozr prevents thermal throttling.System Cooling: Connect and synchronize cooling with strategically placed pin-headers - including a dedicated pump-fan header. Fortified PCIe 5.0 x16 MSI PCI Express Steel Armor slots are secured to the motherboard with extra solder points to support the weight of heavy graphics cards. When every advantage in games counts, Steel Armor also shields the point of contact from electromagnetic interference: 1 x PCIe 5.0/4.0/3.0 x16 slot (with Steel Armor)

DDR5 Memory Performance, Lightning Gen4 M.2, Shield Frozr, Wi-Fi 6E Connectivity 2 x DDR5 Dual Channel (7200+ MHz OC)* Memory Boost: A fully-isolated DDR circuit delivers pure data signals for optimal gaming and overclocking performance.Memory OC profiles in MSI BIOS are MSI OC LAB optimized and can be easily enabled with auto power settings for optimized memory speed and stability. *1DPC 1R Max. overclocking frequency 7200+ MHz, supports Intel XMP. Gen4 M.2 Connectors The MPG B760I EDGE WIFI motherboard features MSI's Gen4 M.2 slots: 2 x Gen4 x4 64Gbps slots* *1 with M.2 Shield Frozr M.2 Shield Frozr Even the world’s fastest SSDs will automatically slow if thermal throttling firmware detects excessively high temperatures. M.2 Shield Frozr is MSI's most advanced thermal solution, offering the best possible protection to ensure maximum SSD transfer speed performance. Wi-Fi 6E & Bluetooth 5.3 2.5G LAN: A Realtek 2.5Gbps LAN controller delivers a premium network gaming experience.Wi-Fi 6E: Features the latest Intel Wi-Fi 6E module (ultra-low latency, high-bandwidth) & Bluetooth 5.3 technology.USB 3.2 Gen 2 Type-C: Connect to devices and transfer files at high bandwidth rates: 10Gbps.HD Audio: 7.1-Channel High Definition Audio with Audio Boost

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks nice and performs well
reviews.reviewText: Have had this is a gaming machine with an i5 and 3060 for about a year. The small form factor lets it fit into smaller cases (H210 from NZXT is excellent example) and it has been running intensive games at the limits of the hardware since then. Would recommend/use again

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good compact ITX motherboard
reviews.reviewText: This is generally a good compact motherboard for an Mini-ITX PC build. The major benefit for gaming is its ability to have a dedicated graphics card, although not a powerful one. It works fine for games that are not too demanding. Keep in mind that being a small and semi-mobile package, it is not meant for high-power devices. Try to keep the box from overheating. As long it is used as intended, its form factor, stability, and performance are great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great looking itx motherboard
reviews.reviewText: Im very happy with this purchase! Bought new and everything came sealed in pristine condition. 10/10

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bang for the buck motherboard!
reviews.reviewText: Built a very nice little gaming PC with this board when there was a sale and it's a very good little performer. The only downside is that I would heavily suggest learning to organize the front panel connectors as neatly as you can because they get in the way of a lot of components in tightly packed builds.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Killing my cpu
reviews.reviewText: I’m a professional PC Builder i bought this motherboard the first time and swapped my core i7 10700 in after using for 1 year in an Asus prime Z490A 3 days of use the cpu temp was perfect not reaching more than 60 decrees c on the 3rd day i turned on my pc with the Red CPU Light I did all the trouble shooting possible and swapped my cpu in to another rig also show the red cpu light i reached out to intel they sent me a brand new i7 10700 thanks for there great service, and I also replaced the motherboard with the same model installed everything with brand new parts 3 4 days later i got the same red CPU light I tried my best checked if there is any Bent pins in the mother board and it has no visual problem, i’m not gonna argue anymore I’m done with MSI!!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It is great Motherboard then ASUS.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great board at a great price
reviews.reviewText: I like this board for the features it includes for the low price. It was perfect for my 10th gen intel ITX build, and the main reason I chose this over other options was the memory overclocking support and the front panel usb type c port. If you need an ITX 10/11th gen ITX board, this would be my choice 100%

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars great boare but beware
reviews.reviewText: I have this board in a couple of computers. The boards all work well. There is one little tiny issue. Do! not! install! the! Realtech console! This seems to be a problem for MSI only. I have brought this to their attention. Tech support rates a 3. There's one guy there, who has no patience for people. If he's gonna do tech support, he's got to have patience, otherwise I'd put him on service detail to fix stuff. As a person who is totally blind, you have to ask what's up on the board. I've been building computers since the late .80's. It's truly amazing how far and how much stuff they can stuff on a Mobo. Anyway, this Realtech console binds the audio to whatever connection you are using. If you say unplug your headphones going back to speakers, it might work or might not work. This is installed during the Win10 process. So before you do anything else, go to the start menu, and find that sucker, and uninstall it. I returned a couple of boards before I knew what was going on. Anyway, these boards work well, and I have no other issues to report. So far, I'd buy them again. Ray
Compact ITX format, great for small PC Box, has DDR5 support and PCIe 5.0, Work great with i7 13600KF.

I had a i3-10100f laying around. Stepfather wanted a new PC. Slammed the CPU into this B560 mini-itx, overclocked the RAM to 3200mhz (i3-10100f supports only 2666mhz on B460) and it worked! Amazing board. Got it in rebate, otherwise it would have been too expensive for a i3-10100f. I would have been better, otherwise, to buy a Ryzen solution for the same price.

reviews.reviewTitle: Una buena motherboard puede venir en distintos tamaños...
reviews.reviewText: La vida de un crítico es sencilla en muchos aspectos, arriesgamos poco, y tenemos poder sobre aquellos que ofrecen su trabajo y su servicio a nuestro juicio. Esperamos con las críticas negativas – divertidas de escribir y leer- pero la triste verdad que debemos afrontar, es que en el gran orden de las cosas, cualquier basura tiene más significado que lo que deja ver nuestra crítica. Pero en ocasiones el crítico si se arriesga cada vez que descubre y defiende algo nuevo… el mundo suele ser cruel con el nuevo talento, las nuevas creaciones… lo nuevo, necesita amigos. Anoche experimenté algo nuevo, una extraordinaria MoBo de una fuente singular e inesperada, decir sólo que el tamaño y su poder han desafiado mis prejuicios sobre la buena tecnologia subestimaría la realidad.En opinión de este crítico, es nada menos que la mejor MoBo ITX precio beneficio. Sin pensarlo, me compraria de nuevo semegante pieza de tecnologia para futuros builds.10/10

reviews.reviewTitle: Works great with a Core I7 10700k
reviews.reviewText: Been paired with a 10700k in a tower100 case and it is great. Handles the 3080 video card and looks good in a vertical oriented case.

Exelente placa, soporta sin problemas componentes de gama alta, y ni hablar que su tamaño es perfecto para cualquier ITX si acaso lo unico curioso es la ubicacion de la 2nda SSD Nvme que esta atras de la placa fuera de hay todo exelente!
